    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="960"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d960">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/543</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé d’Affaires</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BSC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-12">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">No. 264]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my notes Nos. 252<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d960fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_593">p. 593</ref>.</note> and
                    259 of August 4 and August 9, respectively, stating and explaining the position
                    taken up by His Majesty’s Government in regard to the question of armed
                    merchantmen, I have the honour to state that I have now been informed by
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> that exactly similar
                    instructions were at the same time issued by him to His Majesty’s
                    representatives in practically all neutral countries to address the same
                    communications to the respective Governments to which they were accredited.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BSC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colville Barclay</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
